# Deploy workflow (chefgaa-website)

After completing implementation changes the user asked for, **commit and push to `main` automatically** — do not wait for the user to say "deploy" each time.

## Deploy steps

1. Run `npm run build` and fix any errors first.
2. Commit with a concise message focused on why.
3. Push to `origin main` (Netlify auto-deploys from GitHub).

## Do NOT

- Run `netlify deploy` CLI.
- Push secrets (`.env`, credentials).
- Force-push to `main` unless the user explicitly requests it.

## Live site note

Changes go live on **https://chefgaapos.netlify.app/** (Netlify from this repo).

**go.chefgaa.com** is a separate Azure-hosted site — pushing here does not update that domain until DNS is pointed to Netlify.
